# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Mount Olympus Detailing — environment configuration
#
# Copy to .env.local and fill in. Every variable here is OPTIONAL — the app runs
# and saves estimate requests without any of them. What you lose without each
# one is stated below.
#
# .env.local is gitignored. Never commit real keys.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ── SITE / DOMAIN ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Absolute base URL, no trailing slash. Drives canonical + Open Graph URLs.
# Without it: falls back to http://localhost:3000, so social share previews and
# canonical tags point at localhost.
#
# Your domain — mountolympusdetailing.com — IS registered (GoDaddy, expires
# 2028-02-18) and its DNS is hosted at GoDaddy. It currently serves the old
# GoDaddy Website Builder site. See GODADDY-SETUP.md for the cutover sequence.
#
# Stage first:      NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://app.mountolympusdetailing.com
# Then go live:     NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://mountolympusdetailing.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=


# ── ONLINE BOOKING / CALENDAR ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Public booking page URL. Works with Calendly, Google Calendar appointment
# schedules, Square Appointments, Acuity — anything with a shareable link.
#
# When set: a "Book Your Slot" button appears on the confirmation screen AND in
# the customer's confirmation email.
# When unset: both omit it silently and you schedule by phone. No dead button.
#
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_BOOKING_URL=https://calendly.com/mountolympusdetailing/estimate
NEXT_PUBLIC_BOOKING_URL=


# ── EMAIL (Resend) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Without these: requests still save, but NO email goes out. The confirmation
# screen adapts its wording and the DB row records "skipped:not-configured".
#
# Business notifications default to Luis.rodriguez621@outlook.com (set in
# lib/business.ts) — BUSINESS_EMAIL below only exists to redirect them.
#
# ⚠️  SENDING requires a domain you control. Two options:
#   1. Testing now: use MAIL_FROM=onboarding@resend.dev — Resend's shared
#      sender. It can ONLY deliver to the email on your own Resend account, so
#      register that account with Luis.rodriguez621@outlook.com and owner
#      notifications will work immediately. Customer emails will NOT deliver.
#   2. Production: verify send.mountolympusdetailing.com in Resend, then use
#      MAIL_FROM="Mount Olympus Detailing <hello@send.mountolympusdetailing.com>"
#
#      Use the `send.` SUBDOMAIN, not the root. Your root domain already runs
#      Microsoft 365 mail with a hard-fail (-all) SPF record; verifying a
#      subdomain keeps Resend completely separate and leaves your business
#      email untouched. Exact records: GODADDY-SETUP.md §3a.
# https://resend.com/domains
RESEND_API_KEY=
MAIL_FROM=
BUSINESS_EMAIL=


# ── SMS (Twilio) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Without these: requests still save, no SMS is sent, DB records the skip.
#
# Owner alerts default to the numbers in lib/business.ts:
#   primary (469) 390-1255  — also published on the site as the contact number
#   backup  (469) 203-1543  — NOTIFICATION ONLY, never displayed on the site
#
# The backup is a FAILOVER — it only fires if the primary send fails, so a
# normal lead is one text, not two. Override here if the numbers change.
#
# The backup lives in `internalNotificationTargets` (lib/business.ts), separate
# from the public `business` object, so it cannot leak into a rendered page.
# If you set BUSINESS_PHONE_BACKUP here it stays server-side too — this file's
# values are NOT exposed to the browser (only NEXT_PUBLIC_* vars are).
#
# ⚠️  SMS CANNOT GO LIVE IMMEDIATELY even with these filled in. US A2P 10DLC
# requires brand + campaign registration through Twilio before any
# application-to-person message reaches a US mobile. Approval takes days to
# weeks and requires a published privacy policy plus opt-in language on the
# form (the consent checkbox is already implemented). Start this early.
#
# The app will NOT send a customer SMS unless they ticked the consent box —
# enforced in lib/notify.ts. That is a TCPA requirement. Do not remove it.
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=
# Your Twilio number in E.164, e.g. +14695550123
TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER=
# Owner alert numbers — 10 digits or E.164. Defaults shown above.
BUSINESS_PHONE=
BUSINESS_PHONE_BACKUP=


# ── DATABASE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Defaults to ./data.sqlite. Uses Node's built-in node:sqlite (Node >= 22.5),
# so there is nothing to install.
#
# ⚠️  On Vercel / Netlify / any serverless host the filesystem is ephemeral and
# this database WILL be lost between invocations. Migrate lib/db.ts to Postgres
# before deploying to one — every SQL call is confined to that file.
DATABASE_PATH=


# ── SECURITY ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Salt for hashing client IPs before storage (raw IPs are personal data under
# GDPR). Without it a random salt is generated per process, so rate-limit
# counters reset on every restart. Generate one with:
#   node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
IP_HASH_SALT=


# ── PAYMENTS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# None integrated. The site is quote-only by design: the customer requests an
# estimate, you confirm the price, and you take payment in person or by invoice.
# No processor account, no fees, no PCI scope.
#
# If you later want online deposits, add Stripe here and use Stripe Elements.
# Do NOT reintroduce raw card number / CVC inputs — that puts you in PCI-DSS
# SAQ-D scope. See COMPLETION.md.
